      }
    },
    "n_faq_content_eLwabw": {
      "type": "n_faq-content",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_item_mp6NG9": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "secure_strap": false,
            "heading": "What is the Q-Renew LLLT Helmet?",
            "text": "<p>The Q-Renew LLLT Helmet is a medical-grade light therapy device designed to support healthier hair growth by delivering low-level red light and laser energy directly to the scalp. </p><p>It uses 220 LED diodes and 150 medical-grade, low-level laser diodes to target follicles with clinically studied wavelengths that help stimulate cellular activity, improve scalp circulation, and support thicker, fuller-looking hair over time.</p>",
            "section_id": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_item_t3NcGF": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "secure_strap": false,
            "heading": "How does the technology work?",
            "text": "<p>The Q-Renew LLLT Helmet works by delivering specific red-light wavelengths and low-level laser energy into the scalp, where the follicles absorb the light and convert it into cellular energy. This helps support healthier follicle activity, improve circulation, reduce mild inflammation, and encourage fuller, denser-looking hair over time.</p>",
            "section_id": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_item_EAFyJB": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "secure_strap": false,
            "heading": "How many LEDs does the Q-Renew LLLT Helmet have and what wavelengths?",
            "text": "<p>The Q-Renew LLLT Helmet contains 220 LED diodes that operate at 630 nm, 660 nm, and 680 nm, along with 150 medical-grade, low-level laser diodes that emit light at 655 nm, providing a total of 370 targeted light sources for comprehensive scalp coverage.</p>",
            "section_id": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_item_LjtEUT": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "secure_strap": false,
            "heading": "Can I customize my treatment?",
            "text": "<p>On the LCD screen you’re able to select your desired treatment zone before starting the session. This means you aren’t locked into a single full-head mode. You can choose where you want the light therapy to focus.</p>",
            "section_id": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_item_AmWhYd": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "secure_strap": false,
            "heading": "Where should I fit in the Q-Renew LLLT Helmet in my haircare routine?",
            "text": "<p>Use the Q-Renew LLLT Helmet on clean, dry, product-free hair before applying any styling products, oils, serums, or treatments.</p><p>We recommend using the helmet 5-7 times per week for at least 16 weeks. After that, continue every other day to maintain results. Each treatment lasts 12 minutes and ends automatically.</p>",
            "section_id": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_item_cHY4bn": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "secure_strap": false,
            "heading": "How often can I use my Q-Renew LLLT Helmet?",
            "text": "<p>We recommend using the helmet 5-7 times per week.</p>",
            "section_id": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_item_zNGrCK": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "secure_strap": false,
            "heading": "How long will it take before I start seeing results?",
            "text": "<p>Visible changes take time. Most users should expect to use the helmet consistently for at least 3–6 months before noticing fuller, healthier-looking hair. Like any long-term treatment, consistency is key!</p>",
            "section_id": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_item_AGVVrM": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "secure_strap": false,
            "heading": "How do I charge my Q-Renew LLLT Helmet?",
            "text": "<p>To charge your Q-Renew LLLT Helmet, connect the provided USB-C cable to the charging port, located at the back of the charging base. Plug the other end into a power supply. Only use the provided USB-C cable and a 5V DC adapter for charging.</p><p>When your device is charging, the LCD screen will display the charging status. If inactive, tap the screen to check progress.  The device will take 240 minutes or 4 hours to fully change.</p>",
            "section_id": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_item_aFhwqP": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "secure_strap": false,
            "heading": "How do I properly store my Q-Renew LLLT Helmet?",
            "text": "<p>The best way to store your Q-Renew LLLT Helmet is in a cool, dry place away from direct sunlight. We recommend storing your helmet on the charging base to keep it ready for your next treatment, or in the provided box.</p>",
            "section_id": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_item_dMeKDV": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "secure_strap": false,
            "heading": "What is the best way to clean the Q-Renew LLLT Helmet?",
            "text": "<p>The device can be cleaned with a water-based wipe or a damp, clean cloth. For stubborn stains, we recommend gently wiping with 70% alcohol. Avoid using harsh abrasive cleaners, solvents, or other chemical products as this may harm the device.</p><p><strong>Optional:</strong> For an enhanced cleaning experience, lightly spray the inside of the helmet with the <a href=\"#\">Qure Dermal Mist</a> and gently wipe to help maintain hygiene and freshness. </p>",
            "section_id": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_item_HRgQME": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "secure_strap": false,
            "heading": "Who is the Q-Renew LLLT Helmet not suitable for?",
            "text": "<p>Do not use this product if you are under 18, pregnant, breastfeeding, photosensitive, on light-sensitizing medications, prone to light-triggered headaches or seizures, or have open wounds or infections on the scalp.</p>",
            "section_id": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_item_e6KPtw": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "secure_strap": false,
            "heading": "Does the Q-Renew LLLT Helmet come with a warranty?",
            "text": "<p>We provide a 3-year limited warranty covering defects in materials and workmanship for the Q-Renew LLLT Helmet when purchased directly from Qure Skincare.</p><p>For more information on warranty, please visit <a href=\"#\">Our Warranty Policy</a>.</p>",
            "section_id": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_item_QCdqtq": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "secure_strap": false,
            "heading": "Is it FDA-cleared?",
            "text": "<p>Yes, the Q-Renew LLLT Helmet is FDA-cleared. </p><p>The Q-Renew LLLT Helmet is indicated for the promotion of hair growth in males who have Norwood-Hamilton classifications of IIa–V, and in females with androgenetic alopecia who have Ludwig-Savin Classifications of I–II, and in both, Fitzpatrick Classification of Skin Phototypes I to IV.</p>",
            "section_id": ""
          }
        }
      },
